## Translation Management

### Workflow

```
1. Developer adds key to source language (en.json)
2. Key flagged as "needs translation" for other locales
3. Translator provides translations
4. Translations reviewed and merged
5. Untranslated keys fall back to the source language
6. CI warns about missing translations (don't block, but track)
```

### Rules

- **Never release with mixed languages** on one screen (if a key is untranslated, fall back to the source language entirely, don't show a mix)
- **Context for translators** - include descriptions or screenshots so translators understand where the string appears
- **Max string length** - some languages expand (German is ~30% longer than English; plan for it in UI)
- **Avoid gendered language** where possible ("They submitted" not "He/She submitted")
- **Variable naming in translations** - use descriptive names: `{{userName}}` not `{{0}}`

---

## Mobile-Specific i18n

- **Platform-specific listings** (if applicable) - localize title, description, screenshots for each target market
- **All user-visible outbound copy** - use the user's preferred language
- **Date/time in alerts** - always user's locale and timezone
- **System locale changes** - app responds immediately when user changes device language (no restart required, or minimal restart)
- **Keyboard layout** - support language-specific keyboards (Arabic keyboard for Arabic, etc.)

---

## Checklist Before Adding a New Language

**Principle:** Test every user-facing string and layout in at least two diverse locales before releasing.

[REFERENCE] Common i18n QA checks:

- [ ] All user-facing strings extracted to translation files
- [ ] Translation file created and reviewed by native speaker
- [ ] Pluralization rules correct for the language
- [ ] Date/time/number formatting uses Intl API with correct locale
- [ ] RTL layout tested (if RTL language)
- [ ] Font supports the language's character set
- [ ] Language switcher includes the new language
- [ ] URL routing handles the new language prefix
- [ ] **IF your project is web-facing:** locale/meta tags (e.g. hreflang) set for the new language
- [ ] Form validation copy translated
- [ ] Fault text translated
- [ ] Outgoing notifications and email bodies translated
- [ ] All user-facing content available in new language
